<html 
	xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" 
	xmlns:c="http://www.cruxframework.org/crux" 
	xmlns:a="http://www.cruxframework.org/crux/widgets"
	xmlns:b="http://www.cruxframework.org/crux/gwt"
	xmlns:s="http://www.cruxframework.org/templates/showcase"
>

	<head>
		<title>Rolling Panel</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="style/css/standard.css" />
	</head>

	<body>

		<script type="text/javascript" src="showcase/showcase.nocache.js"></script>

		<b:dockPanel id="centeringPanel" width="100%" spacing="5">
			<b:cell horizontalAlignment="center" direction="north">
				<a:decoratedPanel id="scrollerBorder" horizontalAlignment="center">
					<a:widget>
						<a:rollingPanel id="rollingPanel" width="350" spacing="0">
							<b:image id="image6" url="style/img/climb6.png"/>
							<b:image id="image5" url="style/img/climb5.png"/>
							<b:image id="image4" url="style/img/climb4.png"/>
							<b:image id="image3" url="style/img/climb3.png"/>
							<b:image id="image2" url="style/img/climb2.png"/>
							<b:image id="image1" url="style/img/climb1.png"/>
							<b:image id="image7" url="style/img/climb7.png"/>
							<b:image id="image8" url="style/img/climb8.png"/>
							<b:image id="image9" url="style/img/climb9.png"/>
							<b:image id="image10" url="style/img/climb10.png"/>
							<b:image id="image11" url="style/img/climb11.png"/>
						</a:rollingPanel>
					</a:widget>
				</a:decoratedPanel>
			</b:cell>
		</b:dockPanel>
		<s:info sourcesController="baseSourcesController">
			<s:widgetInfo>
				The RollingPanel is a kind of panel with horizontal or vertical rollover into which you can insert elements beyond of destinated area's limit.
				The DynaTabs for example can explode in tabs number the screen area limit.
			</s:widgetInfo>
			<s:exampleInfo>
				if you click in the side buttons, the elements of the list will be displayed. 
				Looking at the example's source, you can see that we handle the rolling events, in order to roll
				the elements being shown in the list. 
			</s:exampleInfo>
		</s:info>
	</body>
</html>